Description:
We are looking to hire a a Junior Test Analyst to work alongside a team of Business Analysts, Developers and other Test Analysts.
You will review business and technical requirements and prepare test cases;
Execute test cases in a systematic and organised fashion, raising defects and preparing reports on test coverage;
Conduct regular regression testing across CRM, Application Forms, including some testing across frontend platforms and help produce and maintain regression test packs;
Provide help investigating issues in the test and development environments;
Maintain the email template manager; including adding, editing and removing email templates.
Gathering translations for new or updated email templates.
Managing the email template review process with the business and legal teams.
Assist with updating and editing translations within the web content manager
Assist in the management of the “Production Issue Triage” process, which Includes daily review of Pega inbox; CRM ticket creation and linking to ITSM; Issue reproduction for escalated ITSMs in a timely fashion; Issue workaround identification for escalated ITSMs in a timely fashion;
Manage the automation test process for the projects that you are held accountable for, ensuring the new functionality is provided to the automation team before the release is moved to UAT, giving the automation team time to update their tests;
Review and provide sign off of new automation scripts.
KEY SKILLS AND EXPERIENCE
Experience working as a dedicated test analyst within an IT team;
Experience of manual testing
Experience of using a CRM or content management system is desirable;
Basic understanding of waterfall and agile development methodologies;
Able to work effectively with minimal supervision, taking ownership of tasks large and small;
Must be detail oriented

